texts.text: >Deep under the streets of Tokyo lies an abandoned subway station...
>In this forgotten place,
>a girl is chasing emphatically after something...

Wait for me, Mr. Rabbit!
...Mr. Rabbit?
That's peculiar, I thought I saw him come down this way...
All I wanted to do was become friends...
What is this place anyway?
I've never seen such a place...
It's like a giant maze! So many places to hide!
What fun it'd be to play here with friends.
It's perfect for Hide and seek, or tag...
Oh I know! I'll make a wish.
>The girl gets down on her knees in the middle of the subway hub and clasps her hands in prayer.
Dear God,
I would like to play here with a lot of friends.
I want friends that would play with me forever and ever.
Can you make my wish come true?
>As if in answer to the girl's prayer, a bright light begins to flood over the entire area...!
Eeeeew! What is this place, a bats' nest?!
That's right, and it was awful.
No offense or anything, but I'm glad it was you and not me who found this place.
So... why are we here now? Where does this tunnel go?
Whoa? Shionyan didn't tell you?
I thought she was supposed to contact you?
When Shionyan summons me, I just come. No questions asked.
No fuss and no prying, the one quality that makes him stand out among my servants.
I just complimented you for knowing your place. Don't I get a thank you?
Thank you Shionyan!! Thank you!!
You know, somehow I feel like this is gonna end in disaster for them someday...
Alright then, a brief briefing.
Although the incident of the attacks made on humans by the demon Camazotz a while back
was solved, there were parts of it that still remained a mystery,
So just in case, I started to investigate the surrounding area of Camazotz's lair.
And lo and behold, something came up...
A place where the Dragon Stream feels off.
And it's probably underground.
That's why I called ya all here today. We're gonna legit look for this place now.
We're goin' in full force, cuz the last time we went in undermanned it didn't work out so well for us.
Okay, I get the picture. So, how're we going to get underground?
Whoa! Hey Newbie, you okay?!
What's wrong with Newbie?!
I don't know... It looked like something was wrong with Newbie's head and just collapsed...
>Amidst the pain in your head, a voice can be heard...

This way... *Giggle*
That's right, come here.
That voice...
Headache...
Voice? What're ya talkin' about?
Headache? Do ya want some water?
Okay, let's get you somewhere that you can rest. Can you stand up, Newbie?
>The voice echoes deep inside your aching head again...

Come to my garden and play...
You'll do that for me, won't you?
I have to go...
Someone is calling me...
What? Wait, where're you...?!
Huh? Someone's calling you?
You're barely able to stand! Just rest for a while, okay?

C'mon, let me help you...
Whoa!!
>[sys user_name] slaps away Ririn's hand!
...W-What did you do that for?!
Hey! Newbie?!
Something's wrong. Newbie never does anything like that.
Yeah, we have to go after Newbie. Let's go.
...Suddenly you just run off, and now suddenly you stop?
Hey, Newbie! Snap out of it!!
Finally, a response.
What happened?
Where am I?
That's what I was gonna ask you.
You were the one that wandered all the way here mumbling to yourself, remember?
Ignoring all our pleas for you to stop, by the way.
Guys, maybe we should just be glad Newbie's back to normal now.
Though I highly doubt that it was fatigue that caused whatever fit that was.
Aight, we should just call it a day now.
And you Newbie, it's off to bed with you when we get back.
How do we get back though... We came through this way right?
...Wait Megakin! Get back!
The walls... They're closing in on both sides?
He's going to get squashed!
Shit! Devil Download!
Nice! It's holding the walls back!
Megakin come on!
>As Megakin jumps back, the walls on both sides completely close on where he was standing.
Damn... That was close. I thought I was pancake for sure.
Are you alright?
Yeah I'm fine. But there goes our way out.
Finding another way out might be a problem too. Somehow our surroundings changed while we weren't looking.
I could swear the pathways weren't this intricate when we got here.
I did some poking around. Looks like we're the only ones here.
Well, if this station is trying to stop us from going back...
I guess the only way we can go is forward.
Say what?! The walls may close in on us again!
OMG, how did this happen! ...Oh.
...It was all my fault. Sorry.
I couldn't help it, okay?
Oh... Sorry, I didn't mean it like that. You're the victim here just as much as us. I know that.
Not even a little bit apologetic? That's kinda infuriating.
But I guess it isn't you're fault though...
Even so, this weird creepy station is... Huh?
What's wrong?
Nothing. I think I just saw an outlandish little girl, that's all.
What? Where?

The corner of that corridor over there...
Wait, where'd she go?
I don't see anybody there.
That's weird, I thought I saw someone.
A cute blonde little girl in an old fashioned one piece dress.
What are the chances of meeting someone like that in Tokyo? You must be imagining things.
...Yeah, I guess you're right.
Well then, we should get going. I just hope we can find something to help make sense of all this sooner than later.
